- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is also a likely category as the paper presents a dependently typed lambda calculus with explicit substitutions, which is a programming language construct. 
- cs.TL (Type Theory) is a possible category as the paper presents a bidirectional type checking algorithm. 
- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is a possible category as the paper deals with substitutions and normalization, which are relevant to natural language processing. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is a less likely category, but still possible as the paper presents a normalization procedure which could be relevant to machine learning algorithms.
